CareDash, a venture-backed start-up located in Cambridge, MA, is the fastest growing healthcare review website, committed to making it easy to find accessible information that helps patients make the right decision about their healthcare provider. Since 2016, we've built CareDash into the most transparent, accessible, and inclusive healthcare review site and have empowered millions of users to feel informed and confident making important decisions about their healthcare. Join our team and help us further our mission. Trusted reviews. Trusted care.

CareDash is looking for a highly-motivated, savvy intern, who is passionate about healthcare and wellness, to play a key role in our email marketing content. This role is ideal for a marketing and communications enthusiast who is interested in the digital marketing life cycle and wants to work within the general health space. Your responsibilities will include writing, editing, and reviewing copy for emails, as well as managing and optimizing the content, in an effort to uncover what is most interesting and engaging to our subscribers.

This is a paid internship with a flexible start and end date.

Requirements
Successful candidates will have a background in marketing, digital marketing, advertising, communications, journalism, or another related field preferred;
Demonstrated interest in email marketing and digital marketing;
Detail-oriented with an eye for consistency and accuracy;
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills;
Highly productive and proactive with excellent time-management and organization skills;
Ability to work effectively with minimal oversight


Responsibilities
Write copy for emails, such as preheaders and subject lines, to pique the interest of our audience
Write new copy for articles used for email content to give the existing assets a refresh
Manage and optimize email content to drive optimal engagement
Set up email campaigns


Bonus
Interest in healthcare;
Interest in working at a fast-paced, ever changing start-up environment;
Experience with email marketing;
Working knowledge of HTML is a plus in order to set-up and troubleshoot email templates;
SQL skills are not required, but are a plus for analyzing email metrics

At CareDash, we value the whole person and the nuances of unique experience, which is why we encourage potential applicants to apply even if they do not meet all criteria. We are committed to providing inclusive workplaces where people of all races, ethnicity, religions, ages, sex, genders, sexual orientations and physical abilities are welcomed, nurtured, and represented. We value passion, dedication, and a willingness to learn, and understand that ability presents itself in many different ways.

Journey to Your Promised Land, Inc. (JTYPL) is an international nonprofit 501(3) tax exempted organization whose vision is to fight poverty throughout the world by:
Increasing access to educational resources to women and youth;
Promoting gender equality and awareness;
Increasing access to healthcare; and
Providing scholarships and/or grants to women and youth for educational or entrepreneurship purposes.We are an emerging nonprofit looking for social entrepreneurs who are passionate about start-ups. We need ambitious and persistent individuals who want to tackling major social issues and offering new ideas for wide-scale change. Looking for Independent and out of the box thinkers - Those who find what is not working and solve the problem by changing the system, spreading the solution, and persuading entire societies to take new leaps.We need a marketing/communications interns to help market and promote our programs.JTYPL needs an energetic and savvy individual whose primary responsibility includes but not limited to the following:
Design outreach materials including program and event brochures, postcards and posters;
Develop and manage the social media feeds on facebook and twitter;
Develop marketing materials for the upcoming special fundraising events and our annual fundraising event;
Drafts basic public relations materials such as news releases, media alerts, fact sheets, etc.
Assists in the implementation of special and media event planning activities;
Attends and participates in client meetings, media training, meetings, and brainstorming sessions with the board and advisory members;
Assists with administrative duties.Qualifications Marketing background required Current college student majoring in marketing (at least a sophomore) Familiarity with social networking platforms Excellent written and verbal communication skills Availability to work remote. A highly motivated hard working individual Organized, reliable and a team player. Will give college credit if needed. Intern is required to meet with President & CEO weekly and must be located within the DMV (District, Maryland, and/ Virginia)

Crowdfunding Finder is seeking a Marketing Intern to begin as soon as possible. Our intern candidate should have an entrepreneurial and creative mindset, be able to dedicate around 20 hours a week and be interested in the financial industry. Based on performance, the internship can be transitioned to a full time position. 

What will you be doing?
* Digital marketing: manage social media channels (LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram);
* Communications: create content for weekly newsletter and social media channels;
* Marketing Analytics: build performance reports per channel, run analysis and suggest changes;
* Business Development: increase number of social media followers, identify potential leads and prospect to them. 
* Event Planning: create, promote and host events with students, investors, companies offering crowdfunding, etc.
* SEO and UX: Analyze all website data; Conduct thorough keyword research; Optimize for on-page SEO; Create a positive website user experience. Prioritize content that offers significant value. Grow organic traffic.

The Company
Rescue provides behavior change marketing services (or "social marketing") to government, non-profit and corporate organizations. Rescue's current work focuses on tobacco, obesity, violence and alcohol prevention; the promotion of exercise, fresh foods and after school programs; and other products and services that promote healthy living. Rescue’s behavior change campaigns focus on diverse populations within teen (13 - 17), young adult (18 - 26), and adult (18+) populations in both rural and urban areas, resulting in a vast array of campaign styles and strategies.

Rescue is a full-service agency, providing research, strategy, creative, production, web, traditional media, social media, policy change, youth engagement and experiential marketing services to clients in over 25 states and provinces, as well as to federal government agencies.

We believe that marketing can do more than sell goods, it can create good.

The Job
We are looking for a dynamic, high performing Social Media Management Intern to gain hands-on experience in social media marketing and online community management. The ideal candidate has a passion for behavior change, a history of excelling in previous roles, and is capable of working in a fast-paced agency environment.

Day-To-Day Activities
Work with the Social Media Manager to collect culturally relevant content for each of Rescue’s social brands on Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram;
Write creative copy and other communication materials for social media;
Research digital trends and the online behaviors of specific target audiences;
Work closely with the Strategy & Communications Team and Social Media Manager to respond to comments on social media, both positive and negative;
Pull post-campaign user comments and work with the Marketing Analytics team to discuss engagement learnings for client reports;
Assist Social Media Managers in sourcing content for monthly media email newsletters
Track social media performance across multiple platforms and provide insights into what works best.


Required Qualifications
High School Diploma or GED;
A strong interest in social media marketing;
First-hand experience using social media for professional efforts, specifically Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, TikTok and/or Snapchat;
An eye for design and basic experience creating visual content (i.e. Canva);
Working in a fast-paced environment;
Consistent schedule and availability.


Preferred Qualifications
An academic background or strong interest in public health, health communications or policy change efforts;
An academic background or strong interest in marketing, communications, public relations, journalism, creative writing, and/or social media;
Non-tobacco-use is highly preferred because we only have tobacco-free environments and also to be consistent with our tobacco prevention campaign goals.

Location: San Diego, CA; Los Angeles, CA; Seattle, WA; or Sacramento, CA.
Status: Internship (Temporary, Part-Time)
Benefits: Learn more about the benefits of working at Rescue here: http://rescueagency.com/careers/
Travel: None

If you’re ready to join our team of mission driven talent challenging the status quo, we’d love to meet you! Check out our Careers page at rescueagency.com/careers for more information about what it’s like to work at Rescue, and the benefits that we offer to our team members.

The Fine Print

Environment

All business-related environments are tobacco-free. Must have valid driver's license, reliable transportation, and computer and Internet access. Must be available to work non-traditional hours such as late nights and weekends.

Physical Requirements

Able to remain in a sitting position for prolonged periods of time and stoop, bend, reach, climb stairs, and move freely throughout the building for the performance of duties. Able to read from a computer or laptop monitor for several hours at a time including fonts of various sizes from a variety of sources. Able to travel nationwide as needed to meet with clients, coworkers, or attend meetings and seminars. Must be able to move boxed work documents (surveys & materials), up to 40 pounds, in and out of office for travel by car and by air.

The Application
All applications must be submitted through Rescue’s online careers system (unless you qualify to request a reasonable accommodation, as detailed at RescueAgency.com/careers). We do not accept applications via email, mail, fax or in-person delivery. Please send questions to careers@rescueagency.com.

PLEASE NOTE: All email correspondence that you receive from Rescue Agency will be sent through an ‘@rescueagency.com’ email address. We recommend that you disregard any emails posing as authentic Rescue Agency accounts (e.g. @rescueaggency.com or rescueagency.jobs@gmail.com). If you receive a message from a Rescue employee, you can verify the legitimacy of the message by contacting us at careers@rescueagency.com.

